The paper proposes a new learning paradigm for dealing with label ambiguity in real-world applications. This suggests that it could be relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and information retrieval (cs.IR). Among these, machine learning (cs.LG) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a new learning framework. Artificial intelligence (cs.AI) is also likely as the paper deals with real-world applications. Computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) are relevant as they often involve multi-label learning. Information retrieval (cs.IR) is also a possibility as it deals with the problem of label ambiguity.
